videos.description: Northwestern's Joe Gaziano sacks Iowa quarterback Nathan Stanley in the red zone forcing the Hawkeyes to settle for a field goal attempt.
videos.headline: Wildcats defense takes down Stanley

videos.description: Ben Niemann lays the wood on Northwestern running back Justin Jackson in the second quarter.
videos.headline: Iowa LB crushes Jackson

videos.description: Hawkeye quarterback Nathan Stanley hits Matt VanderBerg over the middle for a huge 61-yard gain.
videos.headline: Stanley throws 61-yard strike

videos.description: Iowa's Nathan Stanley finds his wide open tight end Noah Fant in the end zone for the game's first points late in the second quarter.
videos.headline: Stanley to Fant for TD

videos.description: Northwestern head coach Pat Fitzgerald says his needs to stop the big play in the second half.
videos.headline: Fitzgerald wants to limit explosive plays

videos.description: Northwestern running back Jeremy Larkin dives across the pylon to tie the game in the third quarter.
videos.headline: Larkin dives in for TD

videos.description: Wildcats punter Hunter Niswander boots the ball 80 yards setting the Hawkeyes up at their own two-yard line.
videos.headline: Niswander's  punt travels 80 yards

videos.description: Northwestern CB JR Pace intercepts a poorly thrown Nathan Stanley pass  late in the fourth quarter.
videos.headline: Wildcat defense picks off Stanley

videos.description: Northwestern QB Clayton Thorson gets some help from his running back pushing his way into the end zone for the overtime touchdown.
videos.headline: Thorson pushes his way into end zone

videos.description: Wildcats head coach Pat Fitzgerald says that it was too windy to attempt a game-winning drive in the fourth quarter setting Northwestern up for a 17-10 overtime victory.
videos.headline: Fitzgerald explains decision to play for OT
